# 13. Model Versioning

Different versions of models are maintained.

## Example

- Model v1
- Model v2
- Model v3

## Why It Is Useful

- Tracking improvements
- Rollback support
- Experiment comparison

---

# 14. Deployment

Deployment means making the model available for real-world use.

## Examples

- Web applications
- Mobile apps
- APIs
- Cloud services

## Real-Life Example

A spam detection model deployed inside Gmail.

---

# 15. Monitoring & Logging

After deployment, model performance is continuously monitored.

## Monitoring Checks

- Accuracy drop
- Data drift
- Model decay
- Errors

## Example

If user behavior changes:

Old model accuracy may decrease.

Then retraining is needed.

---

# 16. Feedback Loop

New data from production is used to retrain and improve the model.

## Example

Netflix recommendation system improves using:

- New watch history
- User ratings

